Part 1: Code Review & Debugging

What I did:

Fixed missing imports, undefined variables, and Sequelize associations in the starter code.

Ensured server runs without crashes.

Tested API endpoints with Postman.

Solution / Code Changes:

// models/Product.js
const { DataTypes } = require("sequelize");
const sequelize = require("../config/db");
const Supplier = require("./Supplier"); // Added missing import

const Product = sequelize.define("Product", {
    name: { type: DataTypes.STRING, allowNull: false },
    sku: { type: DataTypes.STRING, allowNull: false, unique: true },
    price: { type: DataTypes.DECIMAL(10,2), allowNull: false },
    low_stock_threshold: { type: DataTypes.INTEGER, defaultValue: 10 },
});

Product.belongsTo(Supplier, { foreignKey: "supplier_id" });

module.exports = Product;


Fixed similar issues in Inventory, Warehouse, Supplier models.

API endpoints tested with Postman successfully.

Assumptions:

Endpoints return JSON responses.

Default values for some fields like low_stock_threshold are 10.
